main event: The report describes a sighting of an unidentified object emitting a yellowish-white light and making sweeps southward along the southern constellation at USAF Clark AFB.
interesting points: The object was observed to be of the second magnitude, meaning it was relatively bright.
The object was observed for about 12 minutes before it was no longer visible.
The sighting occurred on a clear, bright night with third moonlight, and the visibility was unlimited.
There was no unusual activity or known air traffic reported.
No further evidence was delivered to the CIN (Central Intelligence Network) at the time of the report.
sighted object: an unidentified object emitting a yellowish-white light
witnesses: CO (Commanding Officer), lookout, and CAPT CLOVIS crew
photographs: no photograph present in the image
